The expected column headers are:

Count

Name

Edition

Condition

Language

Foil

Collector Number

Alter

Playtest Card

Purchase Price

These must be spelled exactly as above, including case. Avoid adding an erroneous space before or after any header. However, the order of the column headers is irrelevant. Just be sure that each column header corresponds with the correct column data. Furthermore, only Name is absolutely required, but it is highly advised that you also include, at least, Count, Edition, Collector Number, and Foil to ensure that you get the correct card and quantity in your collection.

Count requires simply a number. Do not add any decimal seperators to the number.

Name requires the exact name, including punctuation, of the card.

Edition requires the set code rather than the set name. Moxfield uses Scryfall set codes, which can be found here.

